node.text:
Our @usaf_thunderbird_maintainers have completed their first-ever local conversion of an F-16 Fighting Falcon, Tail Number A91-0470.

This process saved time, money, and manpower as well as reduced the completion time by more than 100 days.

For years the maintenance team has had the capabilities to convert a traditional gray F-16 to a Thunderbirds F-16 and in October 2020, the team moved forward with that effort.

An enlisted maintenance team was developed and assigned to the project with one mission... to convert 470.

212 days later, on May 5, 2021, they succeeded.

node.title: Thunderbirds accelerate change with first-ever F-16 conversion

and a culture of inclusiveness and belonging across our Air Force.

I don't have the answers, but I do know there is no room for bigotry, hatred or small mindedness in our force. Period. Every member of our team needs to know we have their back.

So let's start the conversation acknowledging we have many valued Airmen who live and work for One Nation under God, indivisible ... but for them ... without liberty and justice for all.” -Gen. David Goldfein / Chief of Staff, U.S. Air Force

node.text:
Today we had the privilege of flying our Hometown Hero, Captain Richard DePrima, a US Army veteran and FDNY firefighter who responded to the attacks on September 11, 2001. He lost several members of his team that day and stayed behind for two weeks to help separate rubble and debris. 

In response to the events of that day, the U.S. Fire Administration formed the FDNY All-Hazard Incident Management Teams (AHIMT) that respond to local, regional, and national emergencies, natural disasters, and public events. DePrima is the FDNY deputy incident commander and battalion chief in charge of more than 300 firefighters who make up the largest AHIMT in the country. They’ve responded to hundreds of events in the past 20 years including recent wildfires and the COVID-19 pandemic. DePrima has served with FDNY for 26 years and continues to serve today. 

We’re thankful for Battalion Chief DePrima and his team and are grateful we had the opportunity to honor him! 

#WeRemember #WeRemember911

node.text:
New jet, who dis? 

Last week, our team finalized the primary in-house conversion process of another F-16C Fighting Falcon to join our fleet, Tail number A91-362. 

The new in-house conversion process saved time, money, and manpower as well as reduced the completion time by more than 100 days. 

Our maintenance team had been perfecting the capabilities to convert a traditional Combat Air Force F-16 for a few years and in October 2020 moved forward with our first in-house conversion for A91-470, which was completed in May of this year. 

Shortly after, we obtained A91-362 and started the conversion process again with another enlisted maintenance team assigned to the project.

Next stop, the paint shop! 🎨
